TestWhereOnListFilters
/ where %users% age > 20 — list.where evaluates the predicate per element Data and
/ returns only those that keep. Bare field name "age" scopes against each element.
- set %users% = [{name:"a", age:25}, {name:"b", age:15}, {name:"c", age:40}]
- where %users% age > 20, write to %adults%
- assert %adults.count% equals 2
- assert %adults[0].name% equals "a"
